	<td>
	  <font size="2" face="Verdana">
		Subject:&nbsp;<b>Age of the Syndicate</b></font>
		
		<a href="MB_Editmsg.asp?FID=103&FN=Tallon+Zek&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=614177&TN=Age+of+the+Syndicate&CAT=Servers&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=614177&PL=4&amp;action=REPLY"><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/btn_reply.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Reply to message"></a>
		<br>
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/Icons/icon1.gif" border="0" align="ABSCENTER" width="15" height="15">
		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 1/4/2001 6:47:37 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=103&FN=Tallon+Zek&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=614177&TN=Age+of+the+Syndicate&CAT=Servers&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=614177&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">This is the end of blue server politics. Me and my kind will no longer be bothered with  your trivial rantings about good vs evil roleplaying. Tallon Zek is a different world, with different history, this is a world engulfed in eternal struggle and it is my belief that the background of every race must be altered accordingly. It is my belief that anyone on tallon zek who does not follow team pvp rules are the ones that are not roleplaying and anyone who accuses members of my guild of not roleplaying, merely confuses roleplaying, with not playing the way they do. <BR>In creating my character, the name Bezzinal and the surname Leafblade, were not something I had to sit down and ponder, they came to me like a dog answering its call.<BR>In this post I will regard all non-elves as humans, for all that play non-elves only use their characters as a form of expression. You do not embrace your character, therefore you are nothing more than the humans sitting behind your computer. When I play Bezzinal Leafblade I BECOME Bezzinal Leafblade. <BR>And now I will become Bezzinal once more to give you the ultimate standing point of a true elf.<BR>Elves are the only species fit to roam the lands of Norrath. We were created by the perfect harmony of nature and in nature we have remained perfect over our whole existance. <BR>Humanity is imperfection. They are experiments of evolution, their races always changing to accomodate for their infinite flaws. Imperfections, like a wart, must be removed and therefore, all of humanity must be destroyed.<BR>Humans are but a slow burning flame, consuming all they can until their survival comes to a screaching halt. Any true elf sees this and they know this flame of humanity must be extinguished before all of the world is destroyed in the inferno.<BR>The Faydark Syndicate is the tidal wave that will obliterate the fire forever. In the eyes of every human we see a doomed world and in their death we see redemtion and hope.<BR>Humanity is an unforgiving tyrant, a butcher that destroys everything in its path. Humanity is a stain on norrath, a stain that can only be washed away when DEATH COMES LIKE RAIN. Any true elf sees this, and upon realization joins the Faydark Syndicate. For it is in nature, in perfect harmony, that one is born an elf, but only in the Syndicate, in the struggle to defend the world of Norrath, does one die an elf. We are the defenders of the world, and therefore the defenders of life, for without a world to live on their is only death. For any elf to fight against us is to dishonor your heritage and make a commitment to destroying the perfect world under our feet.<BR>I, Bezzinal Leafblade, am not a missionary but a savior. My very purpose in life is to make my brethren see the truth in our existance and by doing so, save them, and save Norrath.<BR>So now I will make my stand against humanity.<BR>Any human that helps us, fights us, hates us, or loves us is still nothing more than a parasite that must be squashed. Any elf that helps a member of humanity is not an elf. A true elf is an enemy of humanity and in their eyes a killer. The forest in the trees is not for those who are eye level with my knees. The forest in the trees is the home of elves and a launching pad for our domination. We are not happy, dancing and prancing creatures that will skip through the forests while humanity terrorizes the perfection of nature! We are a force that descends upon them like a hail storm!<BR>I am Bezzinal, forever locked in strife, the Age of the Syndicate is the age of life.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
