e elves) are at war with every other race. This goes for any other race as well, your true intentions are to destroy all that are not on your team. I myself have forsaken the ways of my diety, and totally ignored the roleplaying ruebrick that accompinied the creation of my character. I even changed the history of the elves, to support my own style of roleplaying, a style that has been adapted by anyone who wants to enjoy team pvp to its fullest. <BR>I have yet to see any other race design a background to explain why they slaughter all that aren't on their team (with the exception of the darks, of course their reason was incorperated into the ruebrick which makes roleplaying a dark pk no challenge at all). However I am not condemning those who don't, because I don't believe you need a reason to play team pvp the way it was meant to be played, I just think it makes it a lot more fun. <BR>And by the way cuto, you say we are killing good while evil runs rampant, well let me tell you this. The "evil" team is non-yellow therefore we attack them just as we would attack any other non-yellow. As far as killing off evil goes, I'd say FS does more evil killing than any other guild. While you bicker about elves not playing the way they are "supposed to," my guild is out taking action against the darks. <BR>I have little respect for cross teaming guilds for their method of roleplaying is the easy road. They are too afraid to give up their passage to non-elven towns, and that is why they choose to stick with good vs evil (cops and robbers) roleplaying.<BR>The true elves will fight until they are the only race left, we are the calm after the storm.<BR>Bezzinal Leafblade says, "You say killing all other races is evil in nature..."in nature," hahaha you can not even begin to comprehend what that means. I am an elf, nature is my teacher, and in its lectures I have learned that there are many things that threaten its perfection, and those things must be eradicated. In nature, natural animals keep their bloodlines strong by fighting for a mate, eating defected offspring etc. etc. Unnatural animals, such as midgets, are nothing more than feeble degenerates that must be destroyed. Nature has always been perfect. There are some that believe perfection doesn't exist, what then is it that turns a tiny seed into a giant tree? What other word would you use to explain the cycles of life that are taking course? trees turn carbon dioxide into oxygen that is a nessesity for us to live, we then take that same oxygen and turn it into carbon dioxide, that is a nessesity for the trees to live. Our vast ocean is inhabited by microorganisms such as algea that regulates the temperature of the entire planet. The slightest imbalance in the oceans, the slightest imperfection, and our whole planet could be plunged into ice age. <BR>The cycles of life are so delicate, so easily disturbed, for they are perfect. We were not put here to simply exist in nature, we were put here to COEXIST WITH nature. In my life I have determined that elves are the only race that choose to coexist, we are the only race that has a niche, therefore the only race that has a right to live. To believe this is to be an elf, to disbelieve this is to follow the path of ignorance that the rest of humanity walks upon, to declare yourself human(note: human and humanity applies to all non-elves, see above if confused). To commit to the life of a non-elf is to commit to the destruction of norrath! <BR>Imperfection is weakness, weakness is destruction, the slaughter of humanity a necessary deduction. I am Bezzinal, forever locked in strife, the Age of the Syndicate is the age of life! </P><P>Bezzinal Leafblade (such a fun character to play!)<BR>Officer of the Faydark Syndicate<BR>enemy to the shorties, and murderer of their kin (even the crack-smoking gnomes of steamfont)<BR>Kill like fire<BR>Cleanse like rain<BR>Faydark Syndicate<BR>Remember our name<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
