		<hr size="1">Well Mr. Syndicate sir,</P><P>I must begin by saying that I play my character based on the JRR Tolkein's point of view, as I am an avid fan of his writings.  Yes, I know that Gnomes weren't the main characters, however, I picture the shorties as the happy and pleasant to be with types.  Your opinion of how the world is or should be played, even though it is wrong, is your interpretation.  My opinion is that the Dwarves are hard working stronger type that enjoy sitting around with friends and talking about lore, or past battles with evil as they sip on their ale.  And finally, Gnomes also hard workers but more in the area of tinkering are happy and friendly folk who stay to themselves for the most part but eventually enjoy travelling the world.  Halflings, are the fun loving stay at home type that adventure shortly after they come of age.  They enjoy sitting and drinking while they tell long stories true or made up is not of consiquence.  Notice how none of these races have the dilluted sense of perfection towards their own race nor do they believe any other race to be perfect.</P><P>Judging by the length of your demented ravings of race perfection, I must say that you seem more like a halfling than any other race.  Your stories of your bretheren of past present and future not only bores me, and makes me start to nod off, but shows just how self absorbed you are.  </P><P>I think that you should take some time and read about my distant cousins the Halflings.  Read about what kind of threat that they are not.  Read about how elves, dwarves and humans got along with peace to destroy the evil that was growing.  Apply this reading towards these "days of strife" and realize that we as a light team can get much more done if we pull together, and though you may not think that the shorter races are not perfect you may find that we are tolerable.</P><P>BTW, I have not seen nor heard of any Faydark Syndicate raids on Nek forest or Field of Bone!  No, you "take the easy" way out and simply raid the newbie zones that border your own.  I have never heard of the FS going out to engage the HR, but I suppose that the battle would turn into a finger pointing match about who is more twinked.</P><P>I say good day to you, and may our paths not cross.  I have sworn to my guild that I will not attack elves that are on the light team, I WILL attack elves from FS.</P><P>Cotu<BR>Gnome Enchanter<BR>Blood Runners</P><P>P.S. Blood Runners is but a name to strike fear into the hearts of those who have grown and lived in the shadows.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
